# CI after push

Whenever you **`git push`** (or ask the user to push) to `origin`, treat **GitHub Actions CI**
as part of done — not optional.

Source of truth: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (jobs: `python`, `frontend`).

## After every push

1. Identify the branch you pushed (e.g. `fix/foo`, `feat/M3-bar`, `main`).
2. Wait for the latest run:

```bash
gh run list --branch <branch> --workflow ci.yml --limit 3
gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status
gh run view <run-id> --json conclusion,status,headSha,url
```

3. **Pass:** both `python` and `frontend` jobs `success` → record run URL in PR comment, bug report, or session summary.
4. **Fail:** read failing job logs (`gh run view <run-id> --log-failed`), fix on the same branch, push again, re-watch until green or user waives.

Do not mark a hotfix **resolved**, a milestone **complete**, or a PR **ready to merge** while CI is red on that branch (unless user explicitly waives via AskQuestion).

## Before the first push (CI parity)

Run the same checks CI runs locally when the change touches Python, frontends, secrets, or workflows:

```bash
uv sync --group dev
bash scripts/check_modal_no_database_url.sh
bash scripts/check_openapi_specs.sh
bash scripts/check_secrets.sh
uv run ruff check apps packages tests
uv run ruff format --check apps packages tests
uv run pyright apps packages tests
uv run pytest tests/unit tests/integration tests/privacy tests/e2e tests/smoke tests/eval
cd apps/chat-rag-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
cd apps/data-management-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
```

Full parity list: [14-hotfix](../.cursor/skills/14-hotfix/SKILL.md) §Main CI, [09-qa](../.cursor/skills/09-qa/SKILL.md) Phase 1.

## Merge to `main`

After merge, watch CI on **`main`** for the merge commit SHA (required for 14-hotfix closure and 15-service-health **H0ci**):

```bash
gh run list --branch main --workflow ci.yml --limit 3
gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status
```

If `main` is red after your merge, **try to fix** (same-session chore commit or follow-up PR) before declaring production health **Overall PASS**.

